1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,500
[LUNA GASPS]

2
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:12,916
[CASSHERN YELLS]

3
00:01:57,375 --> 00:01:58,666
Now then...

4
00:01:58,750 --> 00:02:02,333
Aren't any of you
willing to fight Sophita?

5
00:02:02,416 --> 00:02:04,541
No volunteers at all?

6
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:07,250
[WARRIORBOTS YELL]

7
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:09,500
Come on... let's fight...

8
00:02:09,583 --> 00:02:12,708
There's got to be one of you
is up to the challenge... yes?

9
00:02:12,791 --> 00:02:14,500
[WARRIORBOT 3]
It's the Angel of Ruin!

10
00:02:14,583 --> 00:02:15,583
[WARRIORBOT 4] Sophita!

11
00:02:15,666 --> 00:02:17,750
[CRASHING SOUND]

12
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:19,500
[WARRIORBOT 4 YELLS]

13
00:02:19,583 --> 00:02:22,458
None of you are
willing to fight Sophita?

14
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:23,875
Darn.

15
00:02:23,958 --> 00:02:25,208
[WARRIORBOT 5 SCREAMS]

16
00:02:25,291 --> 00:02:26,750
I don't want
to die yet!

17
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:28,666
Are you sure about that?

18
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:30,208
[WARRIORBOT 5 SCREAMS]

19
00:02:30,291 --> 00:02:33,583
[CRASHING SOUND]

20
00:02:33,666 --> 00:02:35,750
Aww...

21
00:02:35,833 --> 00:02:37,083
[GREEN OGRE]
Your obsession with fighting

22
00:02:37,166 --> 00:02:41,375
has grown troublesome, Sophita.

23
00:02:41,458 --> 00:02:44,333
Or should I say Angel of Ruin?

24
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:47,166
[SOPHITA] I don't
care for that name.

25
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:52,791
It's Sophita... and
I fight because I love it.

26
00:02:52,875 --> 00:02:55,541
What would be
the point in fighting?

27
00:02:55,625 --> 00:02:58,666
The ruin is coming so
why hurry towards it?

28
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:02,750
Because Sophita loves
to fight, nothing more.

29
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:04,791
In a much different
time and place

30
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:07,625
you would have become
a famous warrior...

31
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:09,833
Making a name for
yourself and spreading it

32
00:03:09,916 --> 00:03:13,708
throughtout the land just as
I did protecting Braiking Boss.

33
00:03:13,791 --> 00:03:14,958
But with that
arm of yours

34
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:17,458
you can no longer
fight for yourself...

35
00:03:17,541 --> 00:03:20,000
The ruin has
caught up to you.

36
00:03:21,208 --> 00:03:23,500
[CRUMBLING]

37
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:24,750
[WARRIORBOT 6]
Hey! Watch it!

38
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:27,375
[WARRIORBOT 7]
Don't mock us!

39
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:30,041
[THUD]

40
00:03:30,125 --> 00:03:31,458
[CRASHING SOUND]

41
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:36,500
[GREEN OGRE] That's enough
you couldn't handle her

42
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:39,500
even if you were brand new.

43
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:45,416
One of these days I'll replace
this dreaded arm of mine...

44
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:48,041
When I do I'll cut you down...

45
00:03:48,125 --> 00:03:50,958
I look forward to that day.

46
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:56,416
[SOPHITA LAUGHS]

47
00:04:04,916 --> 00:04:07,625
[CASSHERN THINKING]
Who am I...?

48
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:10,875
One who can only
bring about ruin?

49
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:16,916
What reason do
I have to go on living?

50
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:21,416
I'm the one who took the life
of the Sun that was named Moon.

51
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:23,916
[SOPHITA]
Is it really necessary to

52
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,250
have a reason to live and fight?

53
00:04:29,666 --> 00:04:31,833
You have an exquisite body.

54
00:04:31,916 --> 00:04:33,041
You look brand new.

55
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:36,125
There's not a single
scuff anywhere.

56
00:04:38,708 --> 00:04:40,958
Anyways tell me...

57
00:04:41,041 --> 00:04:44,375
Would you like to
fight Sophita, Mister?

58
00:04:52,708 --> 00:04:55,166
But why not...?

59
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:58,625
What about just a few
minutes of sparring?

60
00:04:58,708 --> 00:05:00,958
I'm sorry.

61
00:05:04,625 --> 00:05:08,875
[SOPHITA] Oh come on! You
look so strong and graceful!

62
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:17,125
I wouldn't say I'm strong...
just unable to die.

63
00:05:21,416 --> 00:05:23,583
Oh my.

64
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:25,416
If you're incapable of dying,

65
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,375
then that means you and
I can go on fighting forever.

66
00:05:28,458 --> 00:05:31,458
Why do you seem
so pleased by that?

67
00:05:31,541 --> 00:05:34,083
It's because...
fighting is wonderful.

68
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:36,666
Fighting is living.

69
00:05:39,416 --> 00:05:41,291
Fighting is the only
thing that Sophita

70
00:05:41,375 --> 00:05:43,250
can enjoy in this life...

71
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:46,500
It truly makes
her feel alive!

72
00:05:48,916 --> 00:05:49,583
[WARRIORBOT 8]
An outsider!

73
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:50,666
[WARRIORBOT 9]
Perfect!

74
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,625
[WARRIORBOT 10]
Hand over those legs.

75
00:05:52,708 --> 00:05:55,041
I do not want to fight.

76
00:05:55,125 --> 00:05:58,416
You heard him...!
Now back off!

77
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:02,000
If you want him,

78
00:06:02,083 --> 00:06:04,500
then you'll have to fight
through Sophita first.

79
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:06,916
[WARRIORBOT 11]
The Angel of Ruin...

80
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,208
Get 'em!

81
00:06:09,583 --> 00:06:10,750
[SOPHITA GRUNTS]

82
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:12,416
[WARRIORBOT 11 YELLS]

83
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:17,208
Go on get out of here!

84
00:06:17,291 --> 00:06:18,666
[THUD]

85
00:06:20,375 --> 00:06:22,666
[WARRIORBOT 10 SCREAMS]

86
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,375
Wow...! You're just what
Sophita hoped you would be!

87
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:41,250
A natural born fighter who is
not afraid of using his talents!

88
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,875
Stay away from me.

89
00:06:55,083 --> 00:07:01,541
But why...
After we've finally met?

90
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:05,291
[CASSHERN THINKING]
I don't get it...

91
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:08,791
It seems like the only thing
that happens here is violence...

92
00:07:08,875 --> 00:07:11,791
Why can't I avoid it?

93
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:14,375
[CRUMBLING]

94
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:30,958
I thought I told you
to stay away from me.

95
00:07:31,041 --> 00:07:33,916
[SOPHITA SIGHS]

96
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,708
I can't do that.

97
00:07:35,791 --> 00:07:37,666
You see...
I can't leave you alone

98
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:40,166
until you
fight me first...

99
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:42,708
Please fight Sophita...

100
00:07:49,208 --> 00:07:51,291
[CASSHERN]
Don't look at me like that.

101
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:55,041
The last thing I want
to do is fight someone...

102
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:59,666
And I certainly don't
want to ruin someone.

103
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:02,166
[SOPHITA]
You don't enjoy it?

104
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:07,791
How can you
not enjoy fighting?

105
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:11,375
I don't really see
how anyone could.

106
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:14,333
Well Sophita likes it...

107
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:18,750
It gets hot right here
whenever I'm fighting...

108
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:22,083
So... that's why... I love it.

109
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:31,208
Then I guess you and I will just
never understand each other.

110
00:08:34,208 --> 00:08:35,333
[CASSHERN]
If someone showed me a way

111
00:08:35,416 --> 00:08:37,291
to avoid fighting altogether...

112
00:08:37,375 --> 00:08:40,208
I'd give up this
body in a second.

113
00:08:40,916 --> 00:08:42,625
[CLANG]

114
00:08:50,916 --> 00:08:52,250
Great now what...?

115
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:55,583
He doesn't want anything
to do with me...

116
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:59,041
This is why Sophita
hates using words...

117
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:03,458
Nobody ever understands
Sophita's feelings.

118
00:09:21,166 --> 00:09:23,125
[GREEN OGRE]
Alright, Sophita, I give.

119
00:09:23,208 --> 00:09:25,250
Let's fight, just
like you wanted.

120
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:28,083
Fine... I'd rather fight
you than no one at all,

121
00:09:28,166 --> 00:09:29,666
so let's do this.

122
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:33,583
[WARRIORBOT 12 YELLS]

123
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:34,291
[SOPHITA LAUGHS]

124
00:09:34,375 --> 00:09:35,416
[WARRIORBOT 14 YELLS]

125
00:09:39,541 --> 00:09:42,083
[SOPHITA] I don't want to
ruin you, I really don't...

126
00:09:42,166 --> 00:09:44,083
But the one I really
want to fight refuses,

127
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:46,875
so I'm left with no choice.

128
00:09:48,875 --> 00:09:50,833
Please forgive me.

129
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:52,958
[WARRIORBOTS GRUNT ANGRILY]

130
00:09:53,041 --> 00:09:58,000
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

131
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:05,416
[CRASHING SOUND]

132
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:11,208
Your skills are as
excellent as ever...

133
00:10:11,291 --> 00:10:12,458
I'm impressed.

134
00:10:12,541 --> 00:10:15,916
Would you rather fight
Sophita... or chat?

135
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,291
Am I good enough for you now?

136
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:20,458
Well... maybe... but...

137
00:10:20,541 --> 00:10:23,333
I doubt Sophita... 
will burn from the battle.

138
00:10:23,416 --> 00:10:27,125
I guess we'll never
know unless we try, huh?

139
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:32,583
You are the
Angel of Ruin.

140
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:36,875
You cant help it that you
must ruin anyone around you.

141
00:10:36,958 --> 00:10:40,833
That sound about
right... Sophita?

142
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:45,208
You become overwhelmed
with passion...

143
00:10:45,291 --> 00:10:47,875
...and excitement.

144
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:54,833
You experience the joy
of living when you fight.

145
00:10:54,916 --> 00:10:56,625
Heh...

146
00:10:56,708 --> 00:11:00,291
That is exactly the kind
of woman that you are.

147
00:11:00,375 --> 00:11:01,916
Come at me!

148
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,541
[GREEN OGRE GRUNTS]

149
00:11:03,625 --> 00:11:04,166
[SOPHITA YELLS]

150
00:11:04,250 --> 00:11:05,333
["PING" SOUND]

151
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:06,458
[SOPHITA GASPS]

152
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:07,916
[GREEN OGRE GRUNTS]

153
00:11:09,416 --> 00:11:10,791
[GREEN OGRE YELLS]

154
00:11:10,875 --> 00:11:13,875
[GREEN OGRE GRUNTS]

155
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:17,125
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

156
00:11:19,166 --> 00:11:21,583
[CRUMBLING]

157
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:26,125
Heh, heh...
You just made it lighter.

158
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:31,500
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

159
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:39,166
Prepare... to be ruined!

160
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:40,333
[SOPHITA GASPS]

161
00:11:53,541 --> 00:11:57,500
But why ...? Your arm!

162
00:11:57,583 --> 00:12:00,125
Oh it's nothing...

163
00:12:00,208 --> 00:12:02,166
Unfortunately.

164
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,958
[SOPHITA GASPS]

165
00:12:04,041 --> 00:12:05,666
[GREEN OGRE YELLS]

166
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:07,083
[CRASHING SOUND]

167
00:12:07,166 --> 00:12:08,375
[GREEN OGRE GRUNTS]

168
00:12:08,458 --> 00:12:09,916
I would expect
nothing less from

169
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:13,125
the one who killed
the Sun named Moon.

170
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:20,000
Tell me, why did
you attack her?

171
00:12:20,083 --> 00:12:22,708
Is it because
you like violence?

172
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:26,333
[GREEN OGRE] That's a
simple enough question.

173
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:28,916
Unlike her,
I actually value my life,

174
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:32,083
so I only get involved in
conflict when I have to,

175
00:12:32,166 --> 00:12:34,250
as opposed to
when I desire it.

176
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:36,666
Still... Answer me.

177
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,750
It was for life...

178
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:41,208
Because if I devour you,

179
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:44,250
I will be able to live
for all eternity...

180
00:12:44,333 --> 00:12:45,583
I planned to lure you out

181
00:12:45,666 --> 00:12:49,375
by using her as bait and
it seems I have succeeded.

182
00:12:49,458 --> 00:12:52,708
So you want to live
like everyone else.

183
00:12:52,791 --> 00:12:54,250
I told you...

184
00:12:54,333 --> 00:12:59,916
I will be revived one day...
and I will cut you to pieces!

185
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:03,708
Sounds like you've become
jaded... about everything.

186
00:13:03,791 --> 00:13:04,791
[GREEN OGRE]
What do you expect

187
00:13:04,875 --> 00:13:06,791
in a world where
nothing is born...?

188
00:13:06,875 --> 00:13:09,333
The only thing
left to do is survive.

189
00:13:09,416 --> 00:13:11,708
[GREEN OGRE GRUNTS]

190
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,416
Then you should leave.

191
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,583
Otherwise the ground
beneath that's your feet

192
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:19,375
will become your grave.

193
00:13:19,458 --> 00:13:21,958
[GREEN OGRE] The coming of
the ruin will soon be upon us,

194
00:13:22,041 --> 00:13:23,458
but it would seem
that battling you

195
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:25,833
only has the potential
for shortening my life.

196
00:13:25,916 --> 00:13:28,000
I must pass.

197
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:38,500
Can any form of joy be found

198
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:41,833
while living in
this kind of a world?

199
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:47,083
The repairman in this
town breaks healthy robots

200
00:13:47,166 --> 00:13:50,458
on a daily basis as
a means of eeking out a life...

201
00:13:50,541 --> 00:13:53,000
Making money by
doing the repairs...

202
00:13:53,083 --> 00:13:57,500
Sophita lived like that
for awhile as well.

203
00:13:57,583 --> 00:13:59,416
Then one day I realized...

204
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:02,125
...that If I make the
effort to break someone

205
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:03,583
I should try to enjoy it...

206
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:06,041
I mean, where's the harm
if we're both passionate,

207
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:09,791
and if we get hurt so what...?
Know what I mean?

208
00:14:09,875 --> 00:14:13,750
But even so fighting isn't
meant to be enjoyable.

209
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:18,500
[SOPHITA] Sophita has become
accustomed to enjoying it.

210
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:23,625
If we must be ruined, I want
to feel good when it happens.

211
00:14:23,708 --> 00:14:28,416
I want to feel excited when
I'm ruined... doing what I love.

212
00:14:43,041 --> 00:14:45,916
[CASSHERN GRUNTS]

213
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:49,083
Are you in pain? What's wrong?

214
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:52,166
[CASSHERN GRUNTS]

215
00:14:54,041 --> 00:14:55,916
Your wound...

216
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,916
It's normal for me...

217
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,791
No matter how hurt I am,
it always heals soon afterward.

218
00:15:00,875 --> 00:15:04,958
Oh my... you sure
are strong. Mister.

219
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:09,125
I can see how dying would be
difficult with that ability.

220
00:15:12,791 --> 00:15:15,208
I'm sorry.

221
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:20,458
[CASSHERN]
Why don't we rest tonight?

222
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:47,458
I love you... Mister...

223
00:15:50,541 --> 00:15:51,500
[SOPHITA GRUNTS]

224
00:15:51,583 --> 00:15:52,583
[CRUMBLING]

225
00:15:54,208 --> 00:15:55,750
[SOPHITA GRUNTS]

226
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:00,041
Come on...

227
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:01,291
Let's fight!

228
00:16:01,375 --> 00:16:02,791
It's the only way Sophita
knows how to share

229
00:16:02,875 --> 00:16:05,583
her feelings with you.

230
00:16:05,666 --> 00:16:08,708
To share...
your feelings?

231
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:17,708
This is my favorite feeling.

232
00:16:17,791 --> 00:16:18,958
[CASSHERN] Don't.

233
00:16:19,041 --> 00:16:20,541
Ready?

234
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:22,875
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

235
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:25,125
[SPLASH]

236
00:16:27,416 --> 00:16:28,333
[CASSHERN] Stop it!

237
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:30,458
[SOPHITA] I can't!

238
00:16:30,541 --> 00:16:32,416
I love you too much!

239
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:36,833
[SOPHITA GRUNTS]

240
00:16:36,916 --> 00:16:38,583
[SPLASH]

241
00:16:44,041 --> 00:16:46,291
[SOPHITA] I'll ruin you...

242
00:16:46,375 --> 00:16:49,541
...because I love you.

243
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:54,916
Just Stop it... That's enough!

244
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,458
I can't...

245
00:16:56,541 --> 00:16:59,666
I feel sorry for you Mister.

246
00:17:01,958 --> 00:17:06,916
That is why...
you must be destroyed!

247
00:17:09,208 --> 00:17:10,375
[SOPHITA GRUNTS]

248
00:17:10,458 --> 00:17:12,375
[SPLASH]

249
00:17:15,125 --> 00:17:17,208
Haven't you had
enough yet...?

250
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:19,791
Don't make me
go all out.

251
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:26,125
It's fine...
Sophita is a strong fighter.

252
00:17:34,666 --> 00:17:38,541
I've ruined countless numbers
of robots in my day...

253
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:41,833
Just like I will
ruin you, Mister.

254
00:17:41,916 --> 00:17:46,083
Because that is what you
desire more than anything else.

255
00:18:02,416 --> 00:18:06,750
[SOPHITA] Wouldn't it be
nice... you could be ruined.

256
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:21,833
[CASSHERN GRUNTS]

257
00:18:23,375 --> 00:18:26,791
Great huh...?

258
00:18:26,875 --> 00:18:29,250
It's wonderful.

259
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:34,541
Why?

260
00:18:34,625 --> 00:18:35,583
[SOPHITA GASPS]

261
00:18:35,666 --> 00:18:37,541
Sophita made your
wish come true

262
00:18:37,625 --> 00:18:39,375
yet you're still
standing here...

263
00:18:39,458 --> 00:18:41,208
How come?

264
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:43,666
I'm so happy...

265
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:47,291
that I didn't
have to harm you.

266
00:18:47,375 --> 00:18:50,333
I stayed who I am this time.

267
00:18:53,125 --> 00:18:56,208
I didn't hurt you in any way...

268
00:18:56,291 --> 00:19:00,375
It's probably because you
never intended to kill me.

269
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,250
[CASSHERN GRUNTS IN PAIN]

270
00:19:17,666 --> 00:19:19,541
Mister...

271
00:19:21,583 --> 00:19:24,083
Please don't die.

272
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:36,958
[SOPHITA]
There was no warmth.

273
00:19:39,416 --> 00:19:41,833
I didn't feel the usual
fire in my chest

274
00:19:41,916 --> 00:19:44,750
when I fought against you.

275
00:19:50,125 --> 00:19:52,416
Sophita has only
grown close to others

276
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:55,625
who have been within
range of her deadly saber...

277
00:19:55,708 --> 00:19:57,500
Until today this saber has been

278
00:19:57,583 --> 00:20:01,708
the only method of
communicating her feelings.

279
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:06,375
[CASSHERN] And yet your
feelings were very clear...

280
00:20:06,458 --> 00:20:08,750
...even without the blade.

281
00:20:11,708 --> 00:20:15,250
The fact is you just
tried to save my life.

282
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,625
And you made
yourself vulnerable

283
00:20:19,708 --> 00:20:22,875
by trying to
help me in a fight.

284
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:30,125
[SOPHITA]
Tell me something.

285
00:20:30,208 --> 00:20:33,750
What is your name, Mister?

286
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:36,125
My name?

287
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:37,625
[SOPHITA]
In all the battles I've been in,

288
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:40,791
I've never once asked
for an opponent's name...

289
00:20:40,875 --> 00:20:44,750
but I no longer
want to fight you.

290
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:48,375
So please tell me... your name.

291
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:53,208
It's Casshern.

292
00:20:54,541 --> 00:20:59,000
[SOPHITA] Casshern...
That's a wonderful name...

293
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:04,166
I'm going now.

294
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:10,875
We'll never have to fight
again... for all eternity.

295
00:21:13,458 --> 00:21:17,125
Please... Don't be sad
you're incapable of dying...

296
00:21:17,208 --> 00:21:18,833
Just live your life
and look forward to

297
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:22,500
meeting Sophita again.

298
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:27,500
So...
Goodbye Casshern.

299
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:53,333
[CASSHERN THINKING]
That day, I learned of one life

300
00:21:53,416 --> 00:21:57,791
that continued onward in
this ever-ruining world.

301
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:07,291
♪ closing song ♪

302
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,458
[CASSHERN]
She says to me...

303
00:23:35,541 --> 00:23:40,416
"You were the one who
led the world into ruin."

304
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:45,791
Next time, The Man who
killed the Sun named Moon.

